              <h1>Join as a thinker</h1>
              <div class="sep-line text-center"><h4>-</h4></div>
              <p>If you are a practitioner in economics, science and technology, politics and law, linguistics, cultural studies, education, or a historian, sociologist or futurist, you can <strong>apply to the LightClock thinker pool.</strong></p>
              <p>LightClock thinkers work on paid assignments in opponent pairs.</p>
              <p>Thinkers find their preferred co-author in our thinker pool via profiles, apps, recommendations and alerts or, alternatively, you can invite a fellow expert from your own network provided the two of you are coming from different backgrounds and fields.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-8 col-md-6">
            <div class="right-box">
              <h1>Order research</h1>
              <div class="sep-line text-center"><h4>--</h4></div>
              <p>LightClock thinkers work on assignments from <strong>think tanks, NGOs, private and public organisations</strong>, as well as <strong>corporate</strong> and <strong>academic</strong> bodies.</p>
              <p>The thinkers access these briefs via the Brief Board and send proposals in duos. When you order research from LightClock, you will be sent a number of proposals from unique pairs of thinkers who can’t wait to combine their expertise in an original and beneficial way.</p>
              <p>What you get from all this hard work and intellectual fun is a paper that no one has ever written before, to answer your question in a new, better way.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
